# Flutter Accounting UI

- Keep permission logic explicit in UI actions (show/hide menu items by role/owner).
- Prefer read-only navigation where editing is not allowed; do not rely only on button labels.
- Reuse existing services/models; avoid duplicating API parsing in screens.
- Keep UI changes minimal: preserve current styles, copy, and navigation patterns.

## Required checks after Dart changes

- Run `flutter analyze` for changed files.
- If reports/accounting screens changed, verify at least one key scenario manually:
  - open student -> transactions -> report open flow;
  - reports list action visibility for current role.
